    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate for LawDog centers on exploiting high-upside matchups against favorable arms, with **Lawrence Butler** standing out as our premier start (74.05). His projection is heavily buoyed by a +10% park factor and a juicy matchup against Leiter, who carries a shaky 4.43 xERA. The dynamic platoon advantage and favorable spot in the order make him an elite play. Similarly, we are leaning into the vulnerability of Buehler tonight; both **Cal Raleigh** (68.75) and **Brendan Donovan** (68.26) receive double-digit efficiency boosts from facing a high-xERA pitcher (5.19), with **Brendan Donovan** specifically benefiting from a +14% platoon edge and the primary spot in the lineup. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains a must-start (67.08); while he faces a tougher arm in Baz, his pedigree and the 90% stolen base probability window\u2014which exploits the pitcher's slow delivery\u2014keep his floor exceptionally high.\n\nThe benching process was dictated by our strict efficiency threshold, with **Jung Hoo Lee** (46.66) serving as the most difficult omission. While he offers a respectable base, he couldn't overcome the drag of facing a dominant arm like Burns, who suppressed his overall ceiling compared to the primary lineup. We are exercising caution with **Yainer Diaz** (42.19) and **Wenceel Perez** (50.77); **Yainer Diaz** is relegated to the bottom of the order and facing a difficult Mejia, while **Wenceel Perez** faces an elite hold-out in Bubic that limits his stolen base upside. Conversely, we are keeping **Taylor Ward** active despite a marginal 54.31 score, as his top-of-the-order positioning provides vital R and RBI insulation. As always, we are monitoring all lineups, particularly with **Geraldo Perdomo** currently dormant on the bench due to the team\u2019s scheduling, and we remain ready to pivot if weather or late scratch news impacts the primary targets like **Gleyber Torres** or **Tyler Freeman**.",
